{
  "id": "class_0039",
  "name": "Quarantine Warden",
  "title_completion": "a Quarantine Warden",
  "flavor_text": "They drew the chalk lines so the sickness would know where it ended and the living began. Now the lines move with them, and the brine in the air remembers every door they ever sealed. The city does not thank its wardens — it simply remains standing.",
